<br>
</td></tr></table><br><p> ]</font><p><a name="1337"><hr><table width=99% border=0><tr bgcolor="#efefef"><td><p><b>Welcome to the future</b> <font size=2>(Score: 1)<br>by Jice-Virago on Friday, March 23 @ 15:16:13 EST<BR>(<a href="user.php?op=userinfo&uname=Jice-Virago">User Info</a>) </font></td></tr><tr><td>More and more I think VI is skewing this game to the large 100 people zerg rush for 3 pieces of loot raid.  Its sad, really, all skill is slowly being beaten out of the game and replaced with claim jumper, PnP, mass charge "tactics".  Fear and hate are now farmed more than ever before by the very people they they supposedly didn't want going there anymore.  Inny is still dead the day he pops, so is cazic.  Once they implement these filters you won't see the lean mean uber guilds using careful planning and strategy,  you will see the zergling rush with click stick res factory to send people back in.  The sad thing is, people will accept this dumbing down of the game and pat them selves on the back for their "mad Skilz" never knowing what it was like to break and clear Fear with 18 people under 52 or to kill a dragon in the old world with 24.  Balance the game to 24-32 person raiding parties, don't make a fix that should have been in day one of release and declare the zerg rush as the one sacred Verant approved tactic.</td></tr></table><br><p> ]</font><p><a name="1342"><hr><table width=99% border=0><tr bgcolor="#efefef"><td><p><b>Re: Welcome to the future</b> <font size=2>(Score: 1)<br>by Tuene on Friday, March 23 @ 19:52:25 EST<BR>(<a href="user.php?op=userinfo&uname=Tuene">User Info</a>) </font></td></tr><tr><td>Chuckle, welcome to the future of the Internet era.<br>
<br>
Hate to say this (and even VI is not completely immune from it either), but with the generic malise in the Internet businesses, everything amounts to doing things with less operational expenses.<br>
<br>
I can guaruntee you from a business side, that dependant on how significant the savings is on bandwidth, that the coder(s) will likely be hailed as a hero and be given a liberal bonus on a successful implementation.<br>
<br>
Even estimating that VI's bandwidth cost is at $500/Mbps, an average savings of only 2Kbps per even 5000 users (lot of assumptions on this figure) during their 95% peak time, is nearly a half a million dollars per year savings which goes straight to their bottom line.<br>
<br>
Even with this aside, it's not going to change much.  The reason a majority of the smaller or even medium sized guilds cannot do the things an uber guild does on a regular basis is simply organization.  More and more are getting the levels, but it's still not happening, people simply aren't as dedicated, don't "care" as much, or a myriad of other reasons, but organizing 32 55+ players in many of these guilds is a difficult as best.<br>
<br>
Only advantage this brings to said guilds is the ability to drag the 50-54's along as well even though they're not going to be nearly as effective in terms of contributing to a mobs being slain.  Trying to field 60 or more members at a time... let alone waiting till the precise time that the uberguild has finished clearing to a god (in someone's example) and suddening KSing it?  Whee, good luck, we're talking hours of gathering alone.<br>
<br>
